<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>i3 FAQ - Individual question feed</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/questions/</link><description>Frequently asked questions and answers about the i3 window manager</description><atom:link href="http://faq.i3wm.org/feeds/question/2114/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Copyright i3, 2012</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sat, 28 Jun 2014 23:34:58 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>LibreOffice presentation done right[TM] with i3</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2114/libreoffice-presentation-done-righttm-with-i3/</link><description>Hi,

I recently presented a slide deck made with LibreOffice.  Not sure if my workflow to have the slides on the external presenter (HDMI1) and the presenter notes on my Notebook's monitor (LVDS1) is optimal?  Precisely, I did the following steps:

 1. Had LO on a workspace on LVDS1, pressed F5 and got both the slides and the presenter notes as tiled windows
 1. Moved the slides to a workspace on HDMI1 
 1. Switched to fullscreen for the presenter notes
 1. Switched to fullscreen for the slides

Sure, that worked but is there an easier way to start a presentation?  A neat i3 config trick to have the slides in fullscreen on the external display and the presenter notes in fullscreen on the internal display?

Cheers and thanks,

RT</description><pubDate>Sat, 29 Jun 2013 17:59:23 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2114/libreoffice-presentation-done-righttm-with-i3/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Anton Anikin for &lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I recently presented a slide deck made with LibreOffice.  Not sure if my workflow to have the slides on the external presenter (HDMI1) and the presenter notes on my Notebook's monitor (LVDS1) is optimal?  Precisely, I did the following steps:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Had LO on a workspace on LVDS1, pressed F5 and got both the slides and the presenter notes as tiled windows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Moved the slides to a workspace on HDMI1 &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Switched to fullscreen for the presenter notes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Switched to fullscreen for the slides&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sure, that worked but is there an easier way to start a presentation?  A neat i3 config trick to have the slides in fullscreen on the external display and the presenter notes in fullscreen on the internal display?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers and thanks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;RT&lt;/p&gt;
