 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2114/libreoffice-presentation-done-righttm-with-i3/?answer=2118#post-id-2118</link><description>Sounds pretty effective to me. If you would like to automate these three extra steps, there are probably ways to do it. You could have a look with `xprop` if the presentation window matches some particular string, and make a `for_window`-rule in your config file. Good luck! </description><pubDate>Sun, 30 Jun 2013 13:32:15 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2114/libreoffice-presentation-done-righttm-with-i3/?answer=2118#post-id-2118</guid></item></channel></rss>